questionDTOs.questionDesc: Identify the type of cookies
questionDTOs.questionTooltip:
Bear in mind that any analytics/tracking of users or their activity is NOT considered strictly necessary by default.
The definition of "strictly necessary cookies" is narrow. Cookies can only be categorized as strictly necessary if they enable:
- log in features
- security features
- load balancing
- critical functionality for the website to work (not all features, but critical)
- media consumption, if no analytics is recorded or the analytics cookies can be separated

questionDTOs.questionDesc: Will the application be integrated with the cookie consent management tool on OneTrust?
questionDTOs.questionTooltip: Any cookies or similar tracking technologies that are not classified as "strictly necessary" are subject to the consent of the individual. OneTrust is Accenture's consent management system for all such technologies, to comply with privacy regulations as they exist around the world. Where non-necessary analytics, performance, advertising, third party or other tracking technologies are used, integration with OneTrust is required.
